You are the bad boy / girl of your school. You
have little faith in yourself and usually find
escape in some sort of addicting substance or
yourself. You would rather torture others
above anything else. You regularly skip
school and when you go, always tend to ditch a
certain class. Some classmates can fear you
while others pity you...and your family. (No
offense) Your cruel behavior and abject
personality tends to single you out from the
crowd...and you prefer life this way at times.
However, lonliness can rear its ugly head and
force you seek a way to silence it. But be
warned, your path is dangerous... but only a
strong person can walk this road.

Some
ideal occupations for you can be a Police
officer, Celebrity (who doesn't love the
badasses?), Wrestler, Polotician, or some sort
of leader. Either way, your destined to be
known by many.

Stunt Monkey's Web Site

 

I'm thinking of getting the hoodie on the Merch page and maybe getting some of the patches to put on my converse. 

 

So at least a few words aren't about Stunt Monkey, I feel this is the appropriate time to say that I might be going to an Alkaline Trio concert. It depends on if my mommy wants to drive me or not. There are two date in the first week of July we might do. One's in Georgia, the other in Charlotte. Tickets are $16-17 dollars in advance if anyone wants to tag along...The Alkaline Trio Website. My mommy said she wanted me to see more live music this summer, so I'm researching not so big bands, as they'll have a better chance of being closer to home. Some of my friends are going to Florida for a really long time, or on a cruise *cough Grier cough* and of course every summer some of them go to Maine. I'm in the middle of creating my own little word to escape the horrible monotony that summer can become. It's coming along fairly well. I haven't gotten to goverments yet, but they should be interesting. I'm supposed to read Lord of the Flies for English 9 Honors. To make the locker room a little more bearable, I'm also trying to tighten up my adorable tum. The only thing I have to worry about now is the dress code XP. I suppose that's all....

 

Oh yes,

...stunt monkey stunt monkey stunt monkey stunt monkey...

guess who's playing at The Orange Peel? Rilo Kiley. Oh, you've never heard of her? She only does one of my favorite songs. you think I'd be excited for them to be coming here, wouldn't you? Yeah. Only there's an age limit. 






We live in a cruel, cruel world.

Your Beauty lies in Contradiction. Controversial, unpredictable, and
never what anyone expects. You appearance and your personality are two
opposite things. Even your appearance sends different signals to different
people. To some you may look innocent and sweet, to others you look mysterious
and intimidating at the same time. No one ever knows what to expect with you.
You are a little bit of everything all mixed together. You can be watching
the football game with the guys one minute and the next out shopping at the
mall. You seem to be almost a different person every time you meet someone, but
at the same time you know exactly who you are and there is always that one
thing that makes you you. You enjoy keeping people guessing and people love how
completely unpredictable you are.

Today was pretty awesome, but I'm not done with it yet. I was really sick last night, like upset stomache, head aches, the whole deal, but I'm better now. I was feeling a little ify this morning, so mommy let me stay home from school. Haleluija. I wrote a song, watched Nightmare Before Christmas and tried not to think about homework. My mommy took me to the grocery store and to other fun little erands. It was nifty cool. I'll update later if anything eventful happens.

HITCHHIKERS GUIDE TO THE GALAXY!

APRIL 29!!

WOOO!

So....erm...yeah. I didn't really do much this weekend, but I thought I should post simply to stop thinking of the stuff I've been thinking of.  So, on Friday I went with Claire to IDES for this stupid event thing...(free cake) I FELT SO DEPRIVED! They had a vending machine in the student kitchen along with a Canada Dry machine. The bathrooms are all new (ie, stalls, toilets, faucets HOT WATER). The classrooms are just nicer. We already knew that they had an all new kickass playground and AC. We should get an award for going to that school when it was just a hole in the wall across the street from the projects. The bathrooms where unusable. There was no hot water. The plumbing only worked on good days. Me and Claire were even in Susan's class when there was no AC. I would get to be like 100 degrees in that front classroom. Oh, the inhumanity. 
Anyway... I already posted about yesterday. Go and read it yourself. Today, so far, I have woken up severly depressed. I know why, but I'm currently in denial. Don't worry, I'll be better by tommorrow. I made a shirt with an iron on transfer. It says "Come see the violence inherent in the system! Help! Help! I'm being repressed!" It's awesome. Well...I guess I need to do my dumbess science homework... I'm stuck at home all day...Yawn. Oh god.

I don't feel like explaining myself.

I am just going to push aside all of the crap and talk about good things. This entry won't be very long.

I am super exited. I got a great deal on CD-R disks and got 100 for $20. Greatness deal. I don't know if anyone on LJ will be pissed off if I talk about Grier a little. Like I said before I really like having someone to walk home with again. We also give him carpool on Tuesday, Wednesday and Thursday. This is driving Emily up the wall, which makes me want to dance with joy. Since Grier and I hang out, I have become her idol and she says everything I say. It's way too hilarious. She is in love with Grier and can't stand that he goes home with me everyday. This is also worrying Blake, since he is in love with me. He was acting very depressed for the times when I didn't sit next to him, and now he is very happy all the time because I am at his table in math. We're still wroking on finding a Blakette so he will stop following me around. It's getting annoying. Ben is weird. That's okay, though. I don't really care. He's nice to me, but is obviously nervous. I'm not really sure why. I don't think he's intimidated by my dog collar, so I'm not really sure why. I think it may be because I'm a girl. He doesn't have much experience with the likes of me, what with being a total dorkwad and all. Is dorkwad one word? I'm confused. The magazine infront of me has a picture of Albert Einstein. I love the little quote from him too "I feel now something like a whore. Everybody wants to know what I am doing, and everybody wants to criticize."   Yay, Albert. He's so awesome. 


Longer than I thought it would be. But still not very long. 




I gots to play some Pinball now.
